[thinking] I’m thinking about the workflow for "newly covered call sites" possibly using a dynamic-access report rather than JaCoCo methods. Should I write a note file? Probably not. I’m considering refining the tests with an instrumented test-side subclass. However, constructors are either package/protected or public. I wonder how Java serialization handles writeObject methods for subclasses. I realize it might require custom handling in the test package, but the dynamic access class would ultimately be a subclass, not the active BCDSAPrivateKey.
